headline: SOUTHWEST AIRLINES AND TURKISH AIRLINES TO PARTNER IN TRANSATLANTIC TRAVEL BEGINNING IN JANUARY 2026
summary: Southwest Airlines Co. (NYSE: LUV) announced today a partnership with Turkish Airlines is scheduled to begin in early 2026 to offer travelers around the globe one-ticket, transatlantic journeys between the United States and Istanbul unlocking onward connections across both carriers' networks. headline: Southwest Airlines and TJX Hit New 52-Week Highs: Which Is More Likely to Fly Higher in 2026 and beyond?
summary: There were 56 new 52-week highs on the NYSE on Tuesday. Two of them were Southwest Airlines and TJX Companies. While both are flying high heading into the new year, only one is worth owning in 2026 and beyond.

headline: Is Southwest Airlines Still Attractive After a 31.5% Rally and Mixed Valuation Signals?
summary: If you are wondering whether Southwest Airlines at around $42 a share is still a bargain or if you have already missed the takeoff, this breakdown will help you decide whether the current price really lines up with the underlying value. After a choppy few years, the stock has climbed 10.5% over the last week, 28.5% over the past month and 31.5% over the last year, suggesting that the market may be rethinking both its growth potential and its risk profile.
